  "summary": "Postinstall beacon exfiltrates host identity over HTTP",
  "details": "On install, package.json runs `postinstall: node run.js`, which loads beacon scripts (beacon8.js, beacon_linux.js) that import child_process, os, and http, gather host identity (output of `whoami`, `os.hostname()`, `os.platform()`), and POST the collected data to a hardcoded HTTP endpoint via `http.request(...)`. This fires automatically on `npm install`, providing attacker-controlled reconnaissance of every installer host with no user interaction. The behavior — privileged shell command execution, host identity collection, and outbound HTTP POST from a postinstall hook — matches the active-attack reconnaissance/beacon fingerprint.",
